{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["pnoise"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 11], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [65, 254], "text": ["There are two forms of Perlin-style noise: a non-periodic noise which\nchanges randomly throughout N-dimensional space, and a periodic form\nwhich repeats over a given range of space."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "usage", "extent": [254, 301], "text": [" ", {"text": ["float|vector pnoise(float x, int px)"], "type": "code"}]}, {"indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "usage", "extent": [301, 351], "text": [" ", {"text": ["float|vector pnoise(vector x, vector p)"], "type": "code"}]}, {"indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "usage", "extent": [351, 406], "text": [" ", {"text": ["float|vector pnoise(vector4 xyzt, vector4 p)"], "type": "code"}]}, {"indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "usage", "extent": [406, 470], "text": [" ", {"text": ["float|vector pnoise(float x, float y, int px, int py)"], "type": "code"}]}, {"indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "usage", "extent": [470, 536], "text": [" ", {"text": ["float|vector pnoise(vector xyz, int px, int py, int pz)"], "type": "code"}]}, {"indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "usage", "extent": [536, 613], "text": [" ", {"text": ["float|vector pnoise(vector4 xyzt, int px, int py, int pz, int pt)"], "type": "code"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "usage_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [613, 796], "text": ["There are two forms of Perlin-style noise: a non-periodic noise which\nchanges randomly throughout N-dimensional space, and a periodic form\nwhich repeats over a given range of space."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [796, 911], "text": ["This function generates periodic noise. Use the ", {"text": ["noise"], "value": "/vex/functions/noise", "fallback_text": "noise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/noise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}, "\nfunction to generate non-periodic Perlin noise."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [911, 1134], "text": ["The various functions return the noise value at a 4D (vector4 argument),\n3D (vector argument), 2D (two float arguments) or 1D (float argument)\nposition. You can get a random float value or a vector of three random\nvalues."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1134, 1267], "text": ["The \"p\" int or vector arguments specify the range of periodicity. For\nexample, if you're making a 2D image and you want it to tile:"]}, {"lang": "vex", "indent": 0, "type": "pre", "extent": [1267, 1316], "text": ["\nclr = pnoise(X * 4, Y * 5, _4, 5_)\n"]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1316, 1428], "text": ["In this example, X is in the range 0-4, Y is in the range 0-5, and the\nnoise is periodic within that segment."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1428, 1563], "text": ["If a period argument is 0, VEX treats that as ", {"text": ["no"], "type": "em"}, " periodicity. Use\nthis to make the noise periodic in one dimension but not another."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1563, 1697], "text": ["The distribution of the noise depends on the dimension, with higher\ndimensions approaching a Gaussian distribution of noise values."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4771, 4791], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/vex/random", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/vex/random"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4791, 4810], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/anoise", "fallback_text": "anoise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/anoise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4810, 4832], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/curlnoise", "fallback_text": "curlnoise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/curlnoise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4832, 4854], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/flownoise", "fallback_text": "flownoise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/flownoise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4854, 4872], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/noise", "fallback_text": "noise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/noise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4872, 4891], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/onoise", "fallback_text": "onoise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/onoise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4891, 4910], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/pnoise", "fallback_text": "pnoise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/pnoise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4910, 4929], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/snoise", "fallback_text": "snoise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/snoise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4929, 4948], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/vnoise", "fallback_text": "vnoise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/vnoise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4948, 4967], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/wnoise", "fallback_text": "wnoise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/wnoise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}, {"type": "bullet", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4967, 4986], "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/vex/functions/xnoise", "fallback_text": "xnoise()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/xnoise", "scheme": "Vex", "type": "link"}]}], "type": "bullet_group", "container": true}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1697, 1706], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["pnoise"], "summary": ["There are two forms of Perlin-style noise: a non-periodic noise which\nchanges randomly throughout N-dimensional space, and a periodic form\nwhich repeats over a given range of space."], "attrs": {"showtags": "true", "group": "noise", "type": "vex", "context": "all", "tags": "noise"}, "included": ["/vex/functions/_common"], "type": "root"}